Package: interpElections
Title: Spatial Interpolation of Electoral Data via Inverse Distance Weighting
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Rogerio", "Barbosa", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "rogerio.barbosa@iesp.uerj.br"),
    person("Lucas", "Gelape", role = "aut"))
Description: Interpolates voting counts and electoral demographics from
    polling locations into census tracts using inverse distance weighting
    with per-zone optimized decay parameters. Travel-time matrices are
    computed via the r5r routing engine. Supports GPU-accelerated
    optimization via torch (ADAM) and CPU fallback via L-BFGS-B.
    Includes end-to-end helpers for Brazilian electoral data that
    auto-download census, electoral, and road network data.
